# Number of distinct n\-digit suffixes generated by iteratively multiplying an integer by 4, where the initial integer is 1\.
https://oeis.org/A362468

## Python
```Python
def a(n):
    s, x, M = set(), 1, 10**n
    while x not in s: s.add(x); x = (x<<2)%M
    return len(s), x
print([a(n) for n in range(1, 11)]) # _Michael S. Branicky_, Apr 22 2023
```
```Python
def A362468(n): return (n+1>>1)+(5**(n-1)<<1) # _Chai Wah Wu_, Apr 24 2023
```
